<h2 style="margin:0 0 16px;font-size:20px;font-weight:600;color:#111;line-height:1.3;">
  {{ notification.title | e }}
</h2>

<p style="margin:0 0 20px;font-size:15px;line-height:1.6;color:#374151;">
  {{ notification.body | e }}
</p>

<p style="margin:0 0 20px;padding:14px;background:#dbeafe;border-left:3px solid #3b82f6;font-size:14px;color:#1e3a8a;line-height:1.5;">
  The key can no longer authenticate against the MCP endpoint.
  Any AI client (Claude Code, Cursor, custom agent) currently using
  this key will start receiving 401 errors on its next request.
  The client will need to be reconfigured with a new key to resume
  working.
</p>

<p style="margin:0 0 8px;font-size:14px;color:#6b7280;font-weight:600;">
  If YOU revoked this key intentionally
</p>
<p style="margin:0 0 20px;font-size:14px;line-height:1.6;color:#374151;">
  No action needed.  This email is the audit-trail companion.
</p>

<p style="margin:0 0 8px;font-size:14px;color:#6b7280;font-weight:600;">
  If you DIDN'T revoke this key
</p>
<p style="margin:0 0 24px;font-size:14px;line-height:1.6;color:#374151;">
  An admin in your org did, or someone gained admin access.
  Check the audit log for who and when.
</p>

<table role="presentation" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0">
  <tr>
    <td style="background:#22c55e;border-radius:6px;">
      <a href="{{ dashboard_url }}/admin/audit-log"
         style="display:inline-block;padding:10px 18px;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:#0a0a0f;text-decoration:none;">
        View audit log →
      </a>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>

<p style="margin:24px 0 0;font-size:13px;color:#9ca3af;line-height:1.5;">
  This alert went only to organization admins.
</p>
